ZH: 我在学校的时候，每天早上都会听到电铃响起。
EN: When I was in school, I would hear the electric bell ring every morning.

ZH: 我办公室的电铃坏了，我们只能用手表来报时。
EN: The electric bell in my office is broken, so we have to use a watch to tell the time.

ZH: 这个电铃铃声很刺耳，我不喜欢它。
EN: The sound of this electric bell is very harsh, I don't like it.

ZH: 小明迟到了，他错过了电铃响的时间。
EN: Xiaoming is late, he missed the time when the electric bell rang.

ZH: 电铃的声音提醒我们该去上课了。
EN: The sound of the electric bell reminds us that it's time for class.

ZH: 老师拨动电铃，宣布今天课程结束。
EN: The teacher rang the electric bell to announce the end of today's class.

ZH: 每天电铃响起的时候，学生都会迅速赶到教室。
EN: When the electric bell rings every day, students quickly rush to the classroom.

ZH: 电铃的声音传遍了整个学校。
EN: The sound of the electric bell echoed throughout the entire school.

ZH: 我小时候最怀念的就是学校电铃的声音。
EN: What I miss most from my childhood is the sound of the electric bell in school.

ZH: 电铃响起，今天的会议准时开始了。
EN: The electric bell rang, and today's meeting started on time.

ZH: 在这家公司里，电铃被用来宣布上下班时间。
EN: In this company, the electric bell is used to announce the time for clocking in and out.

ZH: 电铃的声音太大了，有时候会吓到我。
EN: The sound of the electric bell is too loud, sometimes it scares me.

ZH: 当电铃响起时，所有人都停止了手中的工作。
EN: When the electric bell rings, everyone stops their work.

ZH: 请拨动电铃叫服务员。
EN: Please ring the electric bell to call the waiter.

ZH: 电铃的声音像是叮当作响。
EN: The sound of the electric bell is like a jingle.

ZH: 在这个建筑物里，电铃可以远程控制。
EN: In this building, the electric bell can be controlled remotely.

ZH: 他准备好了，只等着电铃响起就开始比赛了。
EN: He is ready, just waiting for the electric bell to ring to start the competition.

ZH: 电铃的音调太高了，有些人听不清楚。
EN: The tone of the electric bell is too high, some people can't hear it clearly.

ZH: 当电铃长时间响起时，会觉得很刺耳。
EN: When the electric bell rings for a long time, it can be very harsh.

ZH: 电铃的声音使我感到焦虑。
EN: The sound of the electric bell makes me feel anxious.
